  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.56,
      "end": 5.7,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.7,
      "end": 9.38,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 10.58,
      "end": 12.36,
      "text": "Aesop's fable, the boasting traveler.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 14.16,
      "end": 18.74,
      "text": "A man once went abroad on his travels, and when he came home he had wonderful tales to",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 18.74,
      "end": 22.92,
      "text": "tell of the things he had done in foreign countries. Among other things he said he had",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.92,
      "end": 26.92,
      "text": "taken part in a jumping match at Rhodes, and had done a wonderful jump which no one could",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.92,
      "end": 27.1,
      "text": "beat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 27.88,
      "end": 32.76,
      "text": "Just go to Rhodes and ask them, he said. Everyone will tell you it's true. But one of those",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 32.76,
      "end": 36.92,
      "text": "who were listening said, if you can jump as well as all that, we needn't go to Rhodes",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 36.92,
      "end": 43.68,
      "text": "to prove it. Let's just imagine this is Rhodes for a minute and now, jump. Deeds, not words.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 45.26,
      "end": 54.76,
      "text": "End of the boasting traveler, read by Patrick McNeil, Bakersfield, California. www.jacpat.com.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
